From 0ed737dbd7299dd79128c32a394eeed8c821c834 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergiy Shcherbyna <sergey.scherbina@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 11:01:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(v2-native): frame case-class `:`-bodies so ALL member
 methods dispatch

The landed Part-3 dispatch (caseMethodsCell capture + __regmethod__ +
registerTaggedMethod) only worked for a SINGLE member method in a layout
(`case class X(f: T):`) body: parseCaseClass.captureLayout stops at the first
statement separator, so 2nd+ member defs leaked as top-level defs and never
dispatched (`base.size()` -> Stub even though `base.get(4)` worked).

Root cause was in `layout`: the inner type-annotation colon in `(data: List[Int])`
consumed the declHead bit, so the OUTER body colon after `)` never opened the
virtual { } block. Fix: a `:` inside a P/S/X (paren/bracket/ext-receiver) frame is
a type colon and must NOT consume declHead. The outer body colon now frames the
body, so it routes through captureBraced (which already loops over all members).

Verified: mf/main.ssc (imported ByteSlice.get/size) native+ASM = 50,5 (== v1);
collide.ssc = 5,2 (no built-in .size hijack). Native audit over all 193 conformance
cases: 192 identical + 1 FIX (scljet-readonly-pager-btree: Stub-error -> golden),
0 regressions (scljet-memory-vfs stays green). Conformance 171/0, V2 lane 13/13.
---
 v2/lib/ssc1-front.ssc0 | 15 +++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/v2/lib/ssc1-front.ssc0 b/v2/lib/ssc1-front.ssc0
index aefce0f47..50d1ea87a 100644
--- a/v2/lib/ssc1-front.ssc0
+++ b/v2/lib/ssc1-front.ssc0
@@ -2677,8 +2677,19 @@ def layout = (toks) =>
                  else if #seq(v, "effect") then true
                  else declHead)
               else declHead in
-            let declColon = if #seq(k, ":") then inDeclHead else false in
-            let nextDeclHead = if #seq(k, ":") then false else inDeclHead in
+            -- A `:` INSIDE a paren/bracket/ext-receiver frame (P/S/X) is a type
+            -- annotation (`x: Int`, `[A: TC]`, `(self: X)`), NOT a declaration-body
+            -- opener — it must not consume the declHead bit, so the OUTER body colon
+            -- after `)`/`]` still opens the virtual `{ … }` block. Without this,
+            -- `case class X(f: T):` leaves declHead=false at the body colon → the
+            -- body is unframed and its member defs leak as top-level `;`-separated
+            -- defs (only the first is captured; the rest never dispatch → Stub).
+            let inParenLike =
+              if topStackIs("P", stack) then true
+              else if topStackIs("S", stack) then true
+              else topStackIs("X", stack) in
+            let declColon = if #seq(k, ":") then (if inParenLike then false else inDeclHead) else false in
+            let nextDeclHead = if #seq(k, ":") then (if inParenLike then inDeclHead else false) else inDeclHead in
             let nextExtensionHead =
               if #seq(k, "id") then (if #seq(v, "extension") then true else extensionHead)
               else extensionHead in
